The paper focuses on developing a novel eye segmentation method using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The method also incorporates shape prior into the segmentation network training procedure, which involves learning the shape prior from the dataset using VAE-GAN, and leveraging the pre-trained encoder and discriminator to regularize the training of SegNet. This aspect of the method involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the challenges of segmenting eyes from low-quality images in the wild, which relates to multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper highlights the importance of eye segmentation in conveying the emotional state and mental well-being of a person, which falls under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
